20someday%2C%20or%20your%20parents%20will%20die%20someday%2C%20and%20so%20it's%20better%20to%20have%20a%20conversation%20now%20than%20be%20surprised%20by%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EBaby%20boomers%20dominate%20America's%20housing%20market.%20They%20own%20roughly%20%2419.7%20trillion%20worth%20of%20US%20real%20estate%2C%20or%2041%25%20of%20the%20country's%20total%20value%2C%20despite%20accounting%20for%20only%20a%20fifth%20of%20the%20population.%20Millennials%2C%20by%20comparison%2C%20make%20up%20a%20slightly%20larger%20share%20of%20the%20population%20but%20own%20just%20%249.8%20trillion%20of%20real%20estate%2C%20or%2020%25.%20The%20disparity%20is%20a%20product%20of%20both%20their%20relative%20youth%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboomers-buying-homes-blocking-millennials-housing-market-real-estate-prices-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estark%20advantages%20enjoyed%20by%20their%20elders%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Flush%20with%20cash%20from%20prior%20home%20sales%20and%20burgeoning%20stock%20portfolios%2C%20boomers%20can%20afford%20to%20win%20bidding%20wars%20and%20upgrade%2C%20downsize%2C%20or%20collect%20rental%20properties%20like%20Monopoly%20pieces.%20Even%20last%20year%2C%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-house-home-real-estate-mortgage-rates-rent-debt-boomers-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emillennials%20solidly%20in%20their%20peak%20homebuying%20years%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20baby%20boomers%20gobbled%20up%20the%20lion's%20share%20of%20the%20market.%20They%20accounted%20for%2042%25%20of%20buyers%20between%20July%202023%20and%20June%202024%2C%20data%20from%20the%20National%20Association%20of%20Realtors%20found%2C%20well%20outpacing%20millennials'%20measly%2029%25%20share.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoomers%20are%20a%20big%20reason%20Americans%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousing-market-ice-age-higher-home-prices-fewer-sales-inventory-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eare%20stuck%20in%20place%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20People%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbaby-boomers-millennials-housing-market-home-prices-mortgage-rates-inventory-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estaying%20in%20their%20homes%20almost%20twice%20as%20long%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20they%20used%20to%2C%20a%20Redfin%20analysis%20found%2C%20with%20nearly%2040%25%20of%20boomers%20having%20lived%20in%20their%20homes%20for%20at%20least%2020%20years%20and%20another%2016%25%20staying%20put%20for%2010%20to%2019%20years.%20A%20survey%20of%201%2C000%20boomers%20by%20Leaf%20Home%20and%20Morning%20Consult%20found%20that%2068%25%20lived%20in%20homes%20that%20were%20at%20least%20three%20decades%20old%2C%20%26quot%3Bwith%20many%20never%20having%20done%20renovations%20or%20replacing%20major%20appliances%2C%20and%20most%20having%20no%20plans%20to%20move%20or%20make%20any%20type%20of%20home%20improvements.%26quot%3B%20Their%20motivations%20for%20staying%20put%20range%20from%20lifestyle%20preferences%20to%20financial%20savvy.%20A%20number%20of%20surveys%20indicate%20that%20many%20boomers%20want%20to%20age%20in%20place%20rather%20than%20retreat%20to%20a%20nursing%20home%20or%20move%20in%20with%20family.%20They're%20also%20more%20likely%20to%20own%20their%20homes%20free%20and%20clear%2C%20with%20no%20pesky%20mortgage%20payments%20each%20month.%20Even%20if%20they%20do%20pull%20up%20stakes%2C%20they%20might%20hold%20onto%20their%20old%20place%20as%20a%20rental%20property%20rather%20than%20sell.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESoon%2C%20though%2C%20Father%20Time%20will%20force%20the%20generation%20to%20either%20pass%20along%20those%20homes%20to%20lucky%20inheritors%20or%20dump%20them%20on%20the%20market.%20While%20demographers%20emphasize%20that%20this%20will%20be%20more%20of%20a%20glacial%20shift%20rather%20than%20the%20well-publicized%2C%20instantaneous%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousing-market-outlook-prices-supply-baby-boomer-older-homeowners-zillow-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esilver%20tsunami%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20this%20changing%20of%20the%20guard%20%3Cem%3Ewill%3C%2Fem%3E%20happen.%20Between%202025%20and%202035%2C%20boomers'%20numbers%20are%20projected%20to%20decline%20by%2023%25%2C%20or%20about%2015.6%20million%20people%2C%20according%20to%20an%20analysis%20of%20Census%20data%20by%20the%20Harvard%20Joint%20Center%20for%20Housing%20Studies.%20Between%202035%20and%202045%2C%20their%20numbers%20are%20expected%20to%20drop%20by%20another%2047%25%2C%20or%2023.4%20million%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20a%20horizon%20of%20a%20decade%20or%20two%20may%20seem%20a%20long%20way%20off%2C%20financial%20planners%20and%20real%20estate%20agents%20warn%20against%20kicking%20the%20can%20down%20the%20road.%20By%20the%20time%20millennials%20actually%20inherit%20a%20house%20from%20their%20parents%2C%20Westfall%20tells%20me%2C%20it'll%20be%20%26quot%3Btoo%20late%26quot%3B%20to%20figure%20out%20the%20best%20way%20to%20set%20up%20that%20transfer.%20In%20many%20instances%2C%20questions%20around%20the%20fate%20of%20a%20house%20will%20crop%20up%20long%20before%20its%20owner%20dies.%20An%20aging%20baby%20boomer%20may%20be%20forced%20out%20of%20their%20home%20and%20into%20a%20nursing%20home%2C%20leaving%20their%20progeny%20to%20figure%20out%20how%20to%20balance%20paying%20for%20upkeep%20on%20the%20house%2C%20a%20mortgage%20if%20there%20is%20one%2C%20property%20taxes%2C%20and%20the%20necessary%20healthcare.%20Without%20money%20set%20aside%20for%20these%20things%2C%20along%20with%20clear%20instructions%20for%20what%20to%20do%20with%20the%20house%20in%20those%20final%20years%20and%20beyond%2C%20the%20situation%20can%20easily%20devolve%20into%20chaos.%20Unprepared%20millennials%20may%20end%20up%20with%20their%20hands%20tied.%20Ari%20Rubin%2C%20the%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20Flock%20Homes%2C%20a%20company%20that%20bills%20itself%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthis-startup-retirement-solution-single-family-rental-landlords-2022-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bretirement%20solution%26quot%3B%20for%20landlords%20and%20regular%20homeowners%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20warns%20that%20they%20could%20wind%20up%20inheriting%20%3Cem%3Eresponsibility%3C%2Fem%3E%20for%20the%20home%20years%20before%20they%20actually%20assume%20the%20title.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20the%20biggest%20problem%20is%20in%20the%20year%20or%2010%20years%20before%20inheritance%2C%26quot%3B%20Rubin%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMillennial%20inheritors%20are%20often%20eager%20to%20climb%20the%20housing%20ladder%2C%20but%20they%20may%20not%20be%20prepared%20for%20all%20the%20monthly%20costs%20that%20go%20into%20paying%20off%20and%20maintaining%20a%20home%20that's%20a%20few%20rungs%20above%20their%20current%20costs.%20That's%20not%20to%20mention%20the%20big-ticket%20upgrades%20or%20repairs%20that%20are%20often%20required%20after%20someone%20has%20lived%20in%20a%20home%20for%20several%20decades.%20And%20even%20if%20your%20boomer%20parents%20move%20into%20a%20nursing%20home%20or%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fadu-people-share-how-tiny-homes-improved-their-lives-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egranny%20flat%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20your%20backyard%2C%20there%20may%20be%20good%20reasons%2C%20tax-wise%2C%20for%20waiting%20to%20sell%20or%20transfer%20the%20old%20home%20until%20they%20die%2C%20especially%20if%20the%20house's%20value%20has%20appreciated%20a%20lot%20(more%20on%20that%20later).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFlock%20Homes%20offers%20one%20answer%20to%20this%20common%20predicament.%20The%20company%2C%20which%20recently%20raised%20a%20%2420%20million%20Series%20B%2C%20gives%20aging%20homeowners%20(or%20their%20inheritors)%20the%20chance%20to%20exchange%20their%20burdensome%20homes%20for%20a%20stake%20in%20a%20diversified%20real%20estate%20fund%20%E2%80%94%20while%20deferring%20taxes%20%E2%80%94%20through%20a%20little-known%20maneuver%20known%20as%20a%20721%20exchange.%20That's%20far%20from%20the%20only%20option%2C%20though.%20There's%20a%20whole%20cottage%20industry%20devoted%20to%20greasing%20the%20handoff%20of%20homes%20from%20one%20generation%20to%20the%20next%2C%20offering%20products%20designed%20to%20minimize%20Uncle%20Sam's%20ability%20to%20put%20his%20hand%20in%20your%20coffers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20no%20%26quot%3Bcorrect%26quot%3B%20way%20to%20pass%20down%20a%20home.%20For%20some%20families%2C%20a%20simple%20beneficiary%20deed%2C%20which%20transfers%20the%20title%20upon%20death%2C%20will%20do%20the%20trick.%20Others%20will%20need%20to%20make%20more%20complex%20arrangements.%20Setting%20up%20the%20house%20in%20a%20trust%20%E2%80%94%20a%20set%20of%20legal%20documents%20that%20define%20exactly%20who%20gets%20it%20and%20when%2C%20what%20they%20can%20(and%20can't)%20do%20with%20it%2C%20and%20maybe%20even%20set%20aside%20money%20to%20fund%20its%20upkeep%20%E2%80%94%20can%20provide%20a%20road%20map%20for%20inheritors%20and%20nip%20intrafamilial%20squabbling%20in%20the%20bud.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20helps%20provide%20a%20structure%20with%20specific%20direction%20on%20how%20those%20assets%20are%20treated%20after%20they're%20gone%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Jeremy%20Taylor%2C%20who%20manages%20real%20estate%20advisory%20services%20at%20Commerce%20Trust.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20overly%20restrictive%20trusts%20could%20leave%20millennial%20inheritors%20in%20a%20bind.%20Taylor%20cites%20examples%20in%20which%20the%20parents%20dictated%20that%20their%20house%20be%20held%20in%20the%20family%20for%20a%20set%20number%20of%20years%2C%20but%20underestimated%20the%20amount%20of%20money%20they'd%20need%20to%20leave%20behind%20in%20order%20to%20keep%20up%20the%20place%20during%20that%20time.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20trust%20with%20no%20cash%20and%20property%20to%20be%20maintained%2C%26quot%3B%20Taylor%20tells%20me%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20not%20a%20lot%20of%20flexibility%20for%20the%20trustee%20to%20sell.%26quot%3B%20The%20inheritors%20may%20end%20up%20stumbling%20through%20the%20court%20system%20for%20months%20to%20get%20permission%20to%20offload%20the%20property.%20And%2C%20of%20course%2C%20trusts%20can't%20completely%20solve%20the%20family%20tension%20that%20often%20arises%20when%20valuable%20assets%20need%20to%20be%20divvied%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20there's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frich-real-estate-estate-gift-tax-avoidance-wealth-planning-inheritance-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20tax%20question%3C%2Fa%3E.%20One%20of%20the%20preoccupations%20among%20the%20investment%20management%20crowd%20is%20helping%20clients%20dodge%20what's%20known%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Favoid-capital-gains-tax-on-sale-of-home-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecapital%20gains%20tax%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20applies%20to%20the%20profits%20made%20from%20selling%20assets%2C%20like%20homes%20or%20stocks%2C%20that%20have%20grown%20more%20valuable%20over%20time.%20If%20your%20boomer%20parents%20sell%20a%20house%20while%20they're%20alive%2C%20they'll%20have%20to%20pay%20taxes%20%E2%80%94%20as%20much%20as%20nearly%2040%25%20%E2%80%94%20on%20the%20amount%20the%20home%20has%20appreciated%20since%20they%20bought%20it.%20Sure%2C%20the%20first%20%24250%2C000%20to%20%24500%2C000%20of%20those%20gains%20are%20tax-exempt%2C%20depending%20on%20your%20filing%20status%2C%20but%20given%20that%20many%20boomers%20have%20held%20onto%20their%20homes%20for%20decades%2C%20their%20profits%20may%20well%20exceed%20those%20thresholds.%20The%20IRS%20offers%20a%20nifty%20hack%2C%20though%2C%20called%20the%20%26quot%3Bstepped-up%20cost%20basis%2C%26quot%3B%20that%20allows%20inheritors%20to%20sell%20the%20property%20with%20a%20minimal%20tax%20bill.%20When%20a%20homeowner%20dies%20and%20passes%20along%20their%20property%2C%20the%20starting%20point%20used%20in%20those%20capital%20gains%20calculations%20gets%20bumped%20up%20to%20the%20house's%20current%20value%2C%20instead%20of%20the%20value%20at%20which%20it%20was%20purchased.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELet's%20take%20a%20theoretical%20example%3A%20Say%20your%20father%20bought%20a%20home%20back%20in%202010%20for%20%24400%2C000.%20He's%20a%20smart%20guy%2C%20picked%20a%20good%20neighborhood%20in%20an%20up-and-coming%20city%2C%20and%20did%20a%20little%20touching%20up%20of%20the%20home%2C%20so%2015%20years%20later%20the%20house%20is%20worth%20%241.1%20million%2C%20which%20comes%20out%20to%20a%20hefty%20%24700%2C000%20gain.%20If%20he%20sold%20it%20before%20dying%2C%20he'd%20have%20to%20pay%20taxes%20on%20%24450%2C000%20of%20those%20gains%20after%20subtracting%20the%20aforementioned%20exemptions.%20But%20if%20he%20hands%20it%20down%20to%20you%20in%20his%20will%2C%20the%20starting%20point%20value%20of%20the%20house%20gets%20adjusted%20to%20%241.1%20million%20%E2%80%94%20in%20other%20words%2C%20if%20you%20sell%20for%20that%20price%2C%20or%20even%20a%20little%20more%2C%20the%20government%20doesn't%20consider%20you%20to%20have%20%26quot%3Bgained%26quot%3B%20any%20value%20since%20the%20inheritance%2C%20so%20your%20tax%20bill%20is%20nothing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJoe%20Metz%2C%20a%20Bay%20Area%20real%20estate%20agent%20and%20the%20founder%20of%20Senior%20Homeowner%20Solutions%2C%20has%20built%20an%20entire%20second%20career%20out%20of%20helping%20people%20pull%20maneuvers%20to%20avoid%20the%20capital%20gains%20tax.%20But%20for%20people%20who%20decide%20to%20keep%20their%20deceased%20parents'%20home%2C%20he%20says%2C%20there's%20another%20bill%20that%20people%20often%20don't%20consider%3A%20property%20taxes.%20People%20just%20don't%20think%20about%20the%20ongoing%20costs%20of%20homeownership%20as%20much%20as%20they%20should.%20Data%20from%20the%20real%20estate%20analytics%20firm%20Cotality%20found%20that%20the%20median%20annual%20property%20tax%20bill%20has%20jumped%2042%25%20since%202019%2C%20to%20more%20than%20%243%2C000.%20The%20tax%20hits%20can%20be%20especially%20jarring%20in%20Metz's%20home%20base%20of%20California%2C%20where%20they%20typically%20spike%20once%20a%20house%20is%20passed%20down.%20In%20San%20Francisco%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20property%20taxes%20on%20a%20%243%20million%20home%20could%20stretch%20past%20%2430%2C000%20a%20year.%20And%20again%2C%20that%20doesn't%20include%20insurance%2C%20a%20mortgage%2C%20and%20the%20random%20repairs%20that%20often%20crop%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20many%20parents%20want%20their%20kids%20to%20have%20the%20house%2C%20and%20so%20many%20kids%20want%20to%20inherit%20the%20parents'%20house%20%E2%80%94%20until%20they%20hear%20about%20the%20property%20tax%2C%26quot%3B%20Metz%20tells%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELaura%20de%20Vera%2C%20a%2035-year-old%20chef%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20found%20that%20handling%20an%20inheritance%20can%20be%20tough%20even%20when%20all%20the%20specifics%20have%20already%20been%20accounted%20for.%20When%20her%20mother%20died%20from%20cancer%20in%202020%2C%20she%20left%20behind%20a%20trust%20with%20stipulations%20that%20detailed%20how%20long%20de%20Vera's%20stepfather%20could%20live%20in%20her%20old%20house%20and%20how%20the%20proceeds%20from%20a%20sale%20would%20be%20divided%20among%20him%2C%20de%20Vera%2C%20and%20her%20sister.%20She%20also%20accounted%20for%20every%20belonging%2C%20down%20to%20the%20jewelry%20inside%20the%20place.%20%26quot%3BShe%20was%20very%20candid%20and%20just%20very%20practical%2C%26quot%3B%20de%20Vera%20says%20of%20her%20mother.%20De%20Vera's%20stepfather%20opted%20to%20sell%20the%20home%20quickly%20for%20a%20handsome%20gain%2C%20which%20was%20fortunate%20%E2%80%94%20de%20Vera%20says%20she%20was%20lost%20in%20a%20fog%20of%20grief%20for%20months%2C%20and%20had%20to%20devote%20time%20to%20all%20the%20other%20logistics%20that%20come%20with%20death.%20Years%20later%2C%20she's%20still%20grateful%20for%20the%20steps%20her%20mother%20took%20ahead%20of%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20were%20as%20prepared%20as%20you%20possibly%20can%20be%20in%20that%20situation%2C%26quot%3B%20de%20Vera%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20nothing%20my%20mom%20could%20have%20done%20better%2C%20and%20it%20was%20still%20just%20devastatingly%20difficult%20to%20slog%20through%2C%20because%20of%20how%20emotional%20the%20situation%20is.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20some%20millennials%2C%20stressing%20over%20what%20to%20do%20with%20their%20parents'%20assets%20may%20turn%20out%20to%20be%20a%20moot%20point.%20My%20colleagues%20at%20BI%20have%20thoroughly%20reported%20on%20all%20the%20outlays%20that%20eat%20into%20inheritances%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboomers-not-enough-retirement-savings-gen-z-millennials-eldercare-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eliving%20expenses%20during%20retirement%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20senior%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flearning-to-raise-kids-while-caring-for-aging-parents-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecare%20for%20aging%20parents%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhome-renovation-nightmare-home-improvement-contractors-consumer-protection-contract-law-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehome%20repairs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20the%20hundreds%20of%20other%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-tariffs-dynamic-pricing-inflation-costs-china-trade-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eday-to-day%20costs%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20put%20a%20dent%20in%20our%20wallets.%20Given%20the%20rising%20expenses%20of%20growing%20old%20and%20the%20locations%20that%20boomers%20have%20chosen%20to%20spend%20their%20golden%20years%2C%20Daryl%20Fairweather%2C%20the%20chief%20economist%20at%20Redfin%2C%20says%20she's%20skeptical%20of%20the%20idea%20that%20all%20this%20wealth%20will%20trickle%20down%20to%20the%20next%20generation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20some%20of%20it%20is%20going%20to%20kind%20of%20evaporate%2C%20because%20the%20homes%20are%20not%20the%20kind%20of%20homes%20that%20younger%20people%20want%2C%26quot%3B%20Fairweather%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BMaybe%20the%20insurance%20costs%20are%20too%20high%20because%20they're%20in%20climate-risky%20areas%2C%20or%20they%20had%20to%20take%20out%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Freverse-mortgage%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereverse%20mortgages%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20pay%20for%20all%20their%20eldercare%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20which%2C%20in%20the%20most%20extreme%20cases%2C%20could%20mean%20little%20or%20no%20equity%20left%20in%20boomers'%20homes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20won't%20be%20the%20case%20for%20all%20those%20millions%20of%20homes%20scattered%20around%20the%20country%2C%20though.%20Westfall%2C%20the%20broker%20in%20Virginia%20Beach%2C%20says%20homeowners%20in%20his%20area%20are%20keen%20to%20learn%20how%20they%20can%20protect%20their%20wealth%20for%20the%20next%20generation%20%E2%80%94%20so%20much%20so%20that%20he's%20begun%20hosting%20informational%20sessions%20in%20which%20he%20and%20a%20lawyer%20field%20questions%20from%20the%20silver-haired%20set.%20As%20for%20the%20young'uns%2C%20Westfall%20tells%20me%20the%20best%20way%20for%20millennials%20to%20prepare%20for%20the%20future%20is%20to%20simply%20have%20a%20conversation%20with%20their%20parents.%20You%20don't%20have%20to%20frame%20it%20as%20%26quot%3BI%20expect%20something%2C%26quot%3B%20Westfall%20says%2C%20but%20it's%20the%20cleanest%20way%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20what%20should%20be%20a%20blessing%20doesn't%20turn%20into%20a%20nightmare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAtkinson%2C%20the%20homeowner%20in%20Austin%20who%20inherited%20her%20father's%20house%2C%20eventually%20decided%20to%20sell%20to%20a%20neighbor%20who%20had%20helped%20care%20for%20her%20father%20late%20in%20his%20life.%20The%20price%20totaled%20%24200%2C000%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%E2%80%94%20well%20below%20the%20going%20rate%20in%20the%20area%2C%20Atkinson%20admits.%20But%20she%20was%20happy%20to%20leave%20the%20house%20in%20the%20hands%20of%20someone%20who%20felt%20like%20family%2C%20rather%20than%20a%20developer%20intent%20on%20tearing%20it%20down%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-are-new-homes-ugly-construction-builders-design-materials-architecture-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eerecting%20a%20McMansion%3C%2Fa%3E.%20By%20the%20time%20she%20sold%2C%20in%202020%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eshe'd%20spent%20about%20a%20year%20combing%20through%20the%20clutter%20and%20assessing%20her%20next%20move.%20She%20says%20she%20was%20glad%20to%20have%20the%20time%20to%20contemplate%20her%20decision%20instead%20of%20making%20a%20harried%20choice%20in%20the%20weeks%20after%20her%20father's%20death.%20She's%20even%20more%20grateful%20for%20the%20conversations%20she's%20had%20with%20her%20mother%20in%20the%20aftermath.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAtkinson's%20mother%20lives%20in%20a%20small%20Texas%20town%2C%20in%20a%20house%20she%20owns.%20Ever%20since%20her%20ex-husband%20died%2C%20she's%20been%20%26quot%3Bvery%20open%20about%20talking%20about%20death%2C%20which%20I%20think%20is%20really%20nice%20coming%20from%20a%20parent%2C%26quot%3B%20Atkinson%20says.%20Her%20mother%20has%20gone%20through%20her%20possessions%20in%20detail%2C%20explaining%20the%20sentimental%20value%20of%20certain%20objects%2C%20the%20worthlessness%20of%20others%2C%20and%20her%20hopes%20for%20what%20will%20become%20of%20them%20after%20she%20dies.%20And%2C%20of%20course%2C%20she%20has%20a%20will.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20dad%20had%20never%20really%20talked%20about%20dying%20and%20what%20happens%20after%20the%20fact%2C%26quot%3B%20Atkinson%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20having%20that%20open%20communication%20with%20my%20parent%20will%20at%20least%20make%20the%20burden%20of%20what%20happens%20afterward%20easier.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22